      • insertNumber

        public void insertNumber(int n)
        Inserts a new digit in the display. If it is the firstDigit it will replace the value on display, if not, it will be appended to the current value on display.
        Parameters:
        n - the number to be introduced.

      • insertDot

        public void insertDot()
        Inserts the dot decimal separator. It won't allow to have more than one dot at the same time. If it is the firstDigit it will add a 0 to the left.

      • switchSign

        public void switchSign()
        Switches the sign of the value on display. To avoid changing the way the number is presented (number of decimal places for example) this operation is made directly to the String without converting it to double. When expecting the user to introduce a new number pressing the switch sign button will result in the display content being replaced by a '-'.

      • setOperation

        public void setOperation(char op)
        Sets the operation to be calculated and calculates the previous operation if there is one.
        Parameters:
        op - a char ('+', '-', '√ó', or '√∑') indicating the math operation to be set.

      • calculate

        public void calculate()
        Proceeds with the selected operation between the previous value on screen (stored on tempValue) and the current one.

      • clean

        public void clean()
        Cleans the screen (but maintains operation and the stored tempValue).

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Resets the calculator.

      • enterErrorMode

        private void enterErrorMode()
        Makes the calculator enter error mode. To be used during Exceptions. In this mode the display will show "Error" and only pressing the AC button can make it leave this state.
